WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

00:01:30.800 --> 00:01:34.520
=Lady Liberty=

00:01:35.020 --> 00:01:37.980
=Episode 34=

00:01:44.911 --> 00:01:46.955
Bill, please,
and help pack these up, too.

00:01:50.660 --> 00:01:51.260
Sorry,

00:01:51.500 --> 00:01:52.300
I'm so late.

00:01:54.780 --> 00:01:56.940
Then, heat these up again
and bring another pot of tea.

00:01:57.260 --> 00:01:57.580
Okay.

00:02:00.980 --> 00:02:02.780
I saw your call earlier.

00:02:03.044 --> 00:02:04.620
A client suddenly came looking for me,

00:02:05.244 --> 00:02:06.220
and he just kept talking,

00:02:06.220 --> 00:02:07.500
so I couldn't answer your call.

00:02:07.860 --> 00:02:08.260
It's okay.

00:02:12.500 --> 00:02:13.300
How's my mom?

00:02:13.740 --> 00:02:14.780
Did she come back?

00:02:16.140 --> 00:02:18.340
She told me to handle the house.

00:02:20.900 --> 00:02:22.020
So she is not coming back?

00:02:22.580 --> 00:02:23.180
Probably not.

00:02:24.288 --> 00:02:26.220
She's planning to use the money
from selling the house

00:02:26.220 --> 00:02:27.340
to buy a place in Guizhou.

00:02:30.700 --> 00:02:32.020
Then, did she

00:02:32.600 --> 00:02:34.022
ask you to tell me anything?

00:02:36.820 --> 00:02:37.140
No.

00:02:41.420 --> 00:02:42.460
Although she said

00:02:42.622 --> 00:02:44.460
not to let you know
where she's staying now,

00:02:44.540 --> 00:02:46.800
if you really want the address,
I can still give it to you.

00:02:48.740 --> 00:02:49.220
No need.

00:02:50.740 --> 00:02:51.660
She has my number.

00:02:51.740 --> 00:02:52.820
If anything really happens,

00:02:52.820 --> 00:02:53.700
she'll call me.

00:02:56.177 --> 00:02:57.822
You're not planning to see her?

00:03:00.977 --> 00:03:02.555
Maybe after some time.

00:03:21.980 --> 00:03:22.620
You and

00:03:23.220 --> 00:03:23.900
Lawyer Bei...

00:03:25.540 --> 00:03:26.060
We broke up.

00:03:29.644 --> 00:03:31.220
Originally, I thought
I might still have a chance

00:03:31.220 --> 00:03:32.380
to ask you to accept me again.

00:03:34.755 --> 00:03:36.860
After all, my situation now
is different from before.

00:03:38.300 --> 00:03:38.820
But...

00:03:39.511 --> 00:03:41.155
But you have a girlfriend now, right?

00:03:44.780 --> 00:03:45.220
Yes.

00:03:45.755 --> 00:03:47.577
She was the one meeting
a client just now,

00:03:47.940 --> 00:03:49.020
so I drove her to Songjiang.

00:03:49.044 --> 00:03:50.500
Traffic was bad on the way back,

00:03:50.500 --> 00:03:51.555
and I was rushing a bit,

00:03:51.700 --> 00:03:52.900
so I grabbed the wrong cup.

00:03:54.020 --> 00:03:54.940
What does she do?

00:03:55.288 --> 00:03:56.577
She's in business.

00:03:57.900 --> 00:03:58.700
An entrepreneur.

00:03:58.980 --> 00:04:00.740
At a pretty well-known company.

00:04:02.100 --> 00:04:02.700
She...

00:04:03.533 --> 00:04:04.644
She's 11 years older

00:04:05.420 --> 00:04:05.900
than I am.

00:04:08.740 --> 00:04:09.180
Well,

00:04:09.644 --> 00:04:11.340
she must be able to help you a lot.

00:04:15.260 --> 00:04:16.980
She helped arrange everything for me,

00:04:17.300 --> 00:04:19.020
including work, housing,

00:04:19.380 --> 00:04:20.340
and even the car.

00:04:22.180 --> 00:04:23.580
Back when Lawyer Bei got divorced,

00:04:24.060 --> 00:04:24.780
I already thought

00:04:25.220 --> 00:04:27.060
you two would end up
together no matter what.

00:04:28.066 --> 00:04:30.266
If I'd known things
would turn out like this,

00:04:30.488 --> 00:04:32.666
I probably wouldn't
have gotten together with her.

00:04:35.900 --> 00:04:37.500
My breakup with Lawyer Bei

00:04:38.060 --> 00:04:39.300
had nothing to do with you.

00:04:40.888 --> 00:04:42.100
And just because we broke up

00:04:42.244 --> 00:04:44.000
doesn't mean I was going to be with you.

00:04:44.540 --> 00:04:44.980
I know.

00:04:46.660 --> 00:04:47.700
But what I mean is,

00:04:48.222 --> 00:04:50.022
I wouldn't have given up
chasing after you.

00:04:50.460 --> 00:04:51.980
I can't give you that much help.

00:04:54.020 --> 00:04:54.540
I know.

00:04:56.488 --> 00:04:58.060
It's too late to say any of this now.

00:04:59.220 --> 00:05:00.020
And I can't exactly

00:05:00.260 --> 00:05:01.260
accept someone's help

00:05:01.377 --> 00:05:03.133
and then turn around and betray them.

00:05:03.133 --> 00:05:05.044
That would be way too much
like Lawyer Bei.

00:05:05.888 --> 00:05:07.533
Besides, whether I'm sincere or not,

00:05:07.980 --> 00:05:09.540
she can tell, right?

00:05:13.820 --> 00:05:14.700
I wish you

00:05:14.820 --> 00:05:15.420
happiness.

00:05:20.420 --> 00:05:22.460
Once my parents' situation is settled,

00:05:22.577 --> 00:05:24.422
we probably shouldn't
see each other anymore.

00:05:26.111 --> 00:05:27.900
Your girlfriend's company
is doing so well.

00:05:28.377 --> 00:05:30.400
I'm sure her background checks
are thorough too.

00:05:31.377 --> 00:05:32.620
Your former law firm knows

00:05:32.711 --> 00:05:34.444
about what happened between us too.

00:05:34.940 --> 00:05:35.580
So,

00:05:36.460 --> 00:05:37.660
she probably knows as well.

00:05:40.377 --> 00:05:41.222
Alright, then.

00:05:41.580 --> 00:05:43.100
I'll get going first.

00:05:43.444 --> 00:05:44.755
No need to walk me out.

00:05:47.580 --> 00:05:48.500
A sudden client meeting

00:05:48.800 --> 00:05:50.300
and grabbing the wrong coffee cup...

00:05:50.666 --> 00:05:52.711
That was probably her way
of warning you already.

00:05:53.420 --> 00:05:53.780
Bye-bye.

00:06:01.660 --> 00:06:03.980
(Catherine)

00:06:07.180 --> 00:06:07.460
Hello?

00:06:22.420 --> 00:06:23.020
Ling Yikai.

00:06:23.740 --> 00:06:24.340
Ms. Zhao.

00:06:26.740 --> 00:06:27.220
Hello.

00:06:27.822 --> 00:06:29.711
I don't think we've met before, have we?

00:06:30.140 --> 00:06:31.220
May I ask who you are?

00:06:31.266 --> 00:06:32.844
- I...
- Let me introduce you.

00:06:33.820 --> 00:06:34.860
This is our new PR hire.

00:06:34.955 --> 00:06:36.420
The daughter of Yuan from finance.

00:06:38.180 --> 00:06:39.060
Yuan's daughter?

00:06:40.020 --> 00:06:41.020
You're all grown up now.

00:06:41.460 --> 00:06:42.260
And very pretty too.

00:06:42.822 --> 00:06:44.060
Are you heading out together?

00:06:44.288 --> 00:06:45.820
Yeah. We're going to Dingqi Platform.

00:06:46.420 --> 00:06:47.780
I'm planning to introduce Xiaoxue

00:06:47.780 --> 00:06:49.300
to the contact person
at Dingqi Platform.

00:06:51.133 --> 00:06:52.933
Xiaoxue, wait for us a moment then.

00:06:53.620 --> 00:06:54.740
Ling Yikai, walk me upstairs.

00:06:55.222 --> 00:06:56.620
My shoes are a little slippery today.

00:06:56.700 --> 00:06:57.777
I'd better be careful.

00:06:59.700 --> 00:07:01.100
Xiaoxue, wait for me in the car.

00:07:05.911 --> 00:07:07.022
I'll be quick.

00:07:12.400 --> 00:07:14.022
When did you hire a PR person?

00:07:14.133 --> 00:07:15.511
How come I didn't know?

00:07:15.644 --> 00:07:17.066
She just started yesterday.

00:07:17.422 --> 00:07:19.100
You should stop
running around so much lately

00:07:19.100 --> 00:07:20.688
and stay home to focus on the baby.

00:07:21.100 --> 00:07:22.540
Don't mess around where you work.

00:07:23.066 --> 00:07:24.660
Yuan handles the company's finances.

00:07:24.660 --> 00:07:26.577
Don't turn the company
into some kind of mess.

00:07:26.777 --> 00:07:28.340
I know. You don't need to lecture me.

00:07:28.644 --> 00:07:30.200
So, why won't you let this Xiaoxue go?

00:07:30.940 --> 00:07:31.700
Go where?

00:07:32.155 --> 00:07:33.740
We're just superior and subordinate.

00:07:33.900 --> 00:07:34.540
Just coworkers.

00:07:35.400 --> 00:07:36.777
Do you think I'm stupid?

00:07:37.380 --> 00:07:38.700
She's exactly your type.

00:07:42.940 --> 00:07:44.940
Yeah. She's obedient and considerate.

00:07:46.377 --> 00:07:48.770
With someone that promising,
it'd be a waste not to mentor her.

00:07:48.780 --> 00:07:50.244
Besides, Yuan will thank me for it.

00:07:50.700 --> 00:07:51.460
Ling Yikai,

00:07:52.444 --> 00:07:53.740
what are you even saying?

00:07:53.940 --> 00:07:55.311
What are you trying to pull now?

00:07:55.900 --> 00:07:56.820
You grew up

00:07:56.820 --> 00:07:57.940
without your parents around.

00:07:58.380 --> 00:07:59.820
You wouldn't want your two children

00:07:59.820 --> 00:08:01.844
to grow up without
a proper family too, right?

00:08:03.980 --> 00:08:04.820
Zhao Lanxin,

00:08:06.020 --> 00:08:07.900
I'll behave myself and know my place.

00:08:08.980 --> 00:08:09.980
You're pregnant now.

00:08:09.980 --> 00:08:11.355
I'll take good care of you.

00:08:11.444 --> 00:08:12.420
Once the babies are born,

00:08:12.420 --> 00:08:13.933
I'll take good care of all of you.

00:08:14.660 --> 00:08:15.140
It's true.

00:08:16.060 --> 00:08:17.460
Family, children, Grandma...

00:08:17.460 --> 00:08:19.130
You've found the perfect way
to control me.

00:08:19.140 --> 00:08:20.260
But you can't stop me

00:08:20.711 --> 00:08:22.155
from admiring and appreciating

00:08:22.177 --> 00:08:23.355
girls who are better than you

00:08:24.820 --> 00:08:26.100
and kinder than you.

00:08:27.940 --> 00:08:28.660
But don't worry.

00:08:28.660 --> 00:08:29.700
I won't cross the line.

00:08:30.220 --> 00:08:31.660
You won't find a single fault in me.

00:08:38.666 --> 00:08:39.820
I'll walk you out.

00:08:49.020 --> 00:08:52.740
(Lingqi Reading Platform.
Massive story collection, constantly updated)

00:08:57.300 --> 00:09:00.380
(Lingqi Reading Platform.
Read the world)

00:09:05.780 --> 00:09:07.700
(Lingqi)

00:09:12.060 --> 00:09:16.260
(Download Lingqi AI Novel
Reading Platform Now)

00:09:16.260 --> 00:09:17.044
What's this?

00:09:17.800 --> 00:09:19.466
You saw it on your way in too, right?

00:09:19.740 --> 00:09:20.820
Isn't this ridiculous?

00:09:22.660 --> 00:09:24.540
Advertisements for our competitor

00:09:25.020 --> 00:09:27.180
showing up in our own elevator lobby?

00:09:27.355 --> 00:09:28.733
Go ask property management

00:09:28.844 --> 00:09:30.377
what the heck they're thinking.

00:09:30.380 --> 00:09:31.720
Tell them to take all of it down.

00:09:32.140 --> 00:09:32.780
And tell them

00:09:33.500 --> 00:09:34.700
that on our turf,

00:09:34.777 --> 00:09:36.311
this kind of thing isn't allowed.

00:09:40.950 --> 00:09:42.090
Whose computer is this?

00:09:42.100 --> 00:09:45.180
(Dingqi Reading Platform.
Lingqi Reading)

00:09:46.460 --> 00:09:46.860
Mr. Fan,

00:09:47.420 --> 00:09:47.980
it's mine.

00:09:49.340 --> 00:09:50.660
When did you download

00:09:50.660 --> 00:09:51.666
the Lingqi Reading app?

00:09:52.100 --> 00:09:54.020
Just a few days ago. A few days ago.

00:09:54.977 --> 00:09:56.220
Why did you download it?

00:09:58.333 --> 00:09:59.900
To know the enemy and know ourselves.

00:09:59.980 --> 00:10:00.860
Makes work easier.

00:10:00.860 --> 00:10:02.300
Oh, come on.

00:10:02.377 --> 00:10:04.400
"Know the enemy
and know ourselves," huh?

00:10:09.180 --> 00:10:10.020
Did all of you

00:10:10.660 --> 00:10:11.540
download it too?

00:10:12.820 --> 00:10:13.340
Did you?

00:10:16.333 --> 00:10:17.644
I downloaded it too.

00:10:21.288 --> 00:10:22.533
Come on, let's talk.

00:10:22.700 --> 00:10:24.300
Tell me how it feels after using it.

00:10:26.500 --> 00:10:27.620
Mainly because it's free.

00:10:28.340 --> 00:10:30.740
So, the barrier
to trying it is very low.

00:10:31.500 --> 00:10:33.300
That kind of user base is the biggest.

00:10:33.300 --> 00:10:35.620
Advertisers are more willing to invest.

00:10:35.688 --> 00:10:37.200
There are more users, after all.

00:10:37.620 --> 00:10:39.620
The quality of the works
is a bit weaker,

00:10:39.620 --> 00:10:41.020
but they're still readable.

00:10:41.260 --> 00:10:42.580
For some readers,

00:10:42.733 --> 00:10:44.140
reading anywhere is still reading.

00:10:44.820 --> 00:10:46.460
Very few works are irreplaceable.

00:10:47.300 --> 00:10:48.060
I took a look.

00:10:48.088 --> 00:10:49.930
Right now, the content
they're making money from

00:10:49.940 --> 00:10:51.488
is basically very straightforward
at first glance.

00:10:51.500 --> 00:10:52.740
Melodrama, heightened emotions.

00:10:53.700 --> 00:10:56.340
That Lingqi platform of yours...

00:10:56.900 --> 00:10:58.060
With such a huge investment,

00:10:58.180 --> 00:10:59.488
where did you get the money?

00:10:59.700 --> 00:11:00.500
Overseas capital.

00:11:00.860 --> 00:11:01.300
How much?

00:11:02.020 --> 00:11:03.300
Unlimited. Depends on demand.

00:11:03.310 --> 00:11:04.100
What is the demand?

00:11:04.100 --> 00:11:06.088
To quickly swallow up
the Mainland China market.

00:11:09.180 --> 00:11:11.540
That's not something
money alone can achieve.

00:11:12.380 --> 00:11:12.740
True.

00:11:12.980 --> 00:11:15.060
Besides money, there's also technology.

00:11:15.266 --> 00:11:17.420
Before entering the market,
we'd already conducted

00:11:17.420 --> 00:11:19.822
comprehensive big data analysis
on the Mainland China market,

00:11:19.888 --> 00:11:21.820
along with a complete
marketing strategy.

00:11:22.066 --> 00:11:23.420
Also, our strategic partners

00:11:23.420 --> 00:11:24.460
had already been established

00:11:24.460 --> 00:11:25.660
months ago.

00:11:30.740 --> 00:11:31.500
Trying...

00:11:32.260 --> 00:11:33.500
to do everything all at once?

00:11:35.380 --> 00:11:36.860
You will choke.

00:11:38.180 --> 00:11:39.420
For a quick victory,

00:11:39.420 --> 00:11:41.740
without giving competitors
much time to prepare, right?

00:11:43.300 --> 00:11:44.860
And your competitor

00:11:46.980 --> 00:11:48.620
would be Dingqi, right?

00:11:50.260 --> 00:11:52.060
Or perhaps,

00:11:52.820 --> 00:11:53.900
a future partner.

00:12:02.300 --> 00:12:04.300
Fan, when are you planning to retire?

00:12:05.740 --> 00:12:06.020
You...

00:12:06.380 --> 00:12:08.060
You're still building
businesses yourself.

00:12:08.180 --> 00:12:10.060
How could I think about retirement?

00:12:11.220 --> 00:12:13.860
If you can sell Dingqi for a good price,

00:12:14.540 --> 00:12:16.740
then for everyone involved,

00:12:16.740 --> 00:12:18.580
that will already be the best outcome.

00:12:21.860 --> 00:12:23.180
You're trying to take over

00:12:23.500 --> 00:12:24.860
Dingqi in one shot,

00:12:26.940 --> 00:12:28.140
just like how Dingqi once

00:12:28.140 --> 00:12:30.020
took over Zhao Lanxin's
Colorful Culture Media?

00:12:30.866 --> 00:12:32.900
Colorful Culture Media
got to keep its brand name,

00:12:32.900 --> 00:12:35.100
but Dingqi Reading Platform can't stay.

00:12:35.340 --> 00:12:37.060
Everything has to be folded into Lingqi.

00:12:37.580 --> 00:12:38.940
The only difference

00:12:40.460 --> 00:12:41.780
is the way you exit.

00:12:47.780 --> 00:12:48.260
Fan,

00:12:49.660 --> 00:12:51.740
I don't want you leaving in disgrace.

00:12:52.420 --> 00:12:54.780
That's why I came to see you first.

00:12:55.820 --> 00:12:58.220
Dingqi's operating model
is already outdated.

00:12:58.380 --> 00:12:59.100
Outdated

00:13:00.020 --> 00:13:01.300
means being eliminated.

00:13:08.300 --> 00:13:09.500
So your

00:13:10.340 --> 00:13:12.460
advanced business model

00:13:13.380 --> 00:13:14.260
is just money

00:13:14.740 --> 00:13:15.540
plus AI?

00:13:18.700 --> 00:13:19.020
Yes.

00:13:20.380 --> 00:13:21.540
You have people,

00:13:22.060 --> 00:13:22.780
but people

00:13:23.780 --> 00:13:25.380
can be bought with money.

00:13:32.580 --> 00:13:33.700
This was written by AI.

00:13:33.700 --> 00:13:34.820
Go ahead and take a look.

00:13:35.180 --> 00:13:36.900
I've already sent copies

00:13:37.060 --> 00:13:38.860
to He Han, Gu Yan,

00:13:38.977 --> 00:13:40.533
and your other top authors too.

00:13:40.688 --> 00:13:41.577
I'm leaving.

00:13:42.377 --> 00:13:43.511
See yourself out.

00:14:06.820 --> 00:14:07.980
(AI and Novel Writing)

00:14:07.980 --> 00:14:09.540
(Lecturer: He Han)

00:14:09.540 --> 00:14:10.300
This is the last topic

00:14:10.300 --> 00:14:11.900
I want to discuss with everyone today.

00:14:12.460 --> 00:14:13.380
It's not in the slides,

00:14:14.180 --> 00:14:15.220
but recently, I've realized

00:14:15.460 --> 00:14:17.420
this seems to be something
we can no longer avoid,

00:14:17.580 --> 00:14:19.100
something we have no choice but to face.

00:14:20.355 --> 00:14:22.066
Take a look at these three quotes first.

00:14:25.840 --> 00:14:27.220
(Some writing
may look impressive at first glance...)

00:14:27.220 --> 00:14:28.680
(AI can probably write decent novels
but not stories with a true voice...)

00:14:28.680 --> 00:14:29.840
(Writing is enjoyable...)
We all have a choice,

00:14:29.900 --> 00:14:31.300
whether you want to become a writer

00:14:31.540 --> 00:14:32.900
or just someone operating a tool.

00:14:34.300 --> 00:14:35.100
As far as I know,

00:14:35.500 --> 00:14:38.020
Lingqi has already
recruited many new authors

00:14:38.380 --> 00:14:39.900
for AI writing training.

00:14:41.666 --> 00:14:43.644
Have any of you
already signed with them?

00:14:48.540 --> 00:14:49.620
Good. That's fine.

00:14:50.860 --> 00:14:51.860
But have you considered

00:14:52.900 --> 00:14:54.780
what impact this will have on you

00:14:54.866 --> 00:14:56.866
and what consequences it might bring?

00:15:03.555 --> 00:15:05.780
Lingqi Platform also reached out
to me with an offer.

00:15:11.088 --> 00:15:12.400
You want to give it a try?

00:15:14.711 --> 00:15:15.640
I haven't decided yet.

00:15:16.060 --> 00:15:16.660
But honestly,

00:15:16.660 --> 00:15:17.660
it's really tempting.

00:15:19.044 --> 00:15:20.355
And it's not about the money,

00:15:21.020 --> 00:15:22.500
even though they are paying a lot.

00:15:23.820 --> 00:15:25.300
I just feel that with new technology,

00:15:25.300 --> 00:15:27.444
being able to experience it
and master it early

00:15:27.660 --> 00:15:28.500
means a lot to me.

00:15:33.540 --> 00:15:34.380
Well,

00:15:35.644 --> 00:15:37.600
I think as long
as you keep writing seriously,

00:15:37.610 --> 00:15:40.466
three to five years from now,
you could become a really good author.

00:15:41.777 --> 00:15:43.600
And maybe I'm a bit old-fashioned,

00:15:43.980 --> 00:15:45.580
but I believe AI can assist writing,

00:15:45.580 --> 00:15:46.500
not replace it.

00:15:47.111 --> 00:15:49.340
Because writing itself
is slow and painstaking work.

00:15:50.220 --> 00:15:51.740
Only by writing over and over yourself

00:15:51.740 --> 00:15:54.044
do you even stand a chance
of improving little by little.

00:15:54.300 --> 00:15:55.780
But if you let AI write for you,

00:15:55.790 --> 00:15:57.050
and the feedback turns out great,

00:15:57.060 --> 00:15:58.488
then there will be no turning back.

00:15:58.622 --> 00:16:00.511
It's the same logic
as hiring a ghostwriter.

00:16:03.380 --> 00:16:05.660
But after writing
for three or five years,

00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:07.488
there's still no guarantee

00:16:07.490 --> 00:16:08.680
I'll become a good writer.

00:16:08.700 --> 00:16:10.340
Whereas AI-generated writing

00:16:10.420 --> 00:16:12.444
is going to advance rapidly
in the next few years.

00:16:12.660 --> 00:16:14.260
And writers using AI right now

00:16:14.260 --> 00:16:15.660
have already gotten a head start.

00:16:17.060 --> 00:16:17.780
Most likely.

00:16:19.140 --> 00:16:21.060
Isn't that exactly
the dilemma we're facing now?

00:16:21.580 --> 00:16:22.500
There's no safety net.

00:16:22.666 --> 00:16:24.555
It just depends
on which side you're betting on.

00:16:24.622 --> 00:16:26.422
If it were you,
which side would you bet on?

00:16:26.900 --> 00:16:28.500
I'm not you, so how would I know?

00:16:29.340 --> 00:16:29.820
Besides,

00:16:30.300 --> 00:16:31.740
it's a good thing I stepped away early

00:16:31.740 --> 00:16:32.860
and avoided the impact of AI.

00:16:33.540 --> 00:16:34.260
See?

00:16:34.500 --> 00:16:35.860
Getting old has its advantages too.

00:16:38.900 --> 00:16:39.820
Tell me,

00:16:40.622 --> 00:16:43.022
what choice do you think Ms. Lin
would want me to make?

00:16:46.177 --> 00:16:48.355
Obviously, she'd want
you to write your own work.

00:16:51.466 --> 00:16:53.220
Of course, you should write it yourself.

00:16:53.740 --> 00:16:55.060
AI can be your assistant,

00:16:55.620 --> 00:16:57.180
but your own writing ability

00:16:57.460 --> 00:16:59.380
still needs daily practice.

00:17:01.740 --> 00:17:02.940
It's like

00:17:03.020 --> 00:17:04.700
ordering takeout versus home cooking.

00:17:05.066 --> 00:17:06.460
Takeout gives you more variety,

00:17:06.620 --> 00:17:08.980
but it doesn't have the warmth
of a home-cooked meal.

00:17:09.066 --> 00:17:10.555
If you're opening a restaurant,

00:17:10.700 --> 00:17:11.260
it's best

00:17:11.540 --> 00:17:12.860
if you know how to cook yourself.

00:17:14.533 --> 00:17:17.311
You came back halfway through
the intensive course just to ask this?

00:17:18.260 --> 00:17:19.020
Did you ask He Han?

00:17:19.177 --> 00:17:20.155
What did he say?

00:17:22.100 --> 00:17:23.540
He said it depends on personal choice,

00:17:23.933 --> 00:17:26.222
and luckily, he never
had to face this situation.

00:17:27.955 --> 00:17:29.222
So he really quit writing?

00:17:35.822 --> 00:17:37.380
He livestreams and teaches classes now.

00:17:37.511 --> 00:17:39.022
That still earns him some money.

00:17:39.140 --> 00:17:40.660
Plus, he still gets a portion

00:17:41.180 --> 00:17:42.340
of royalties

00:17:42.533 --> 00:17:44.488
and traffic revenue from his old novels.

00:17:45.020 --> 00:17:46.100
So, supporting himself

00:17:46.220 --> 00:17:47.380
basically isn't a problem.

00:17:55.420 --> 00:17:56.260
Ms. Lin, Mei,

00:17:56.820 --> 00:17:58.420
you don't have to move out right now.

00:17:59.222 --> 00:18:01.220
Especially since
you're going abroad later.

00:18:01.380 --> 00:18:03.355
You really shouldn't
bother finding a new place.

00:18:05.022 --> 00:18:06.380
I just want to live somewhere

00:18:06.380 --> 00:18:07.860
closer to my mom's hospital.

00:18:09.555 --> 00:18:11.111
What about you, Mei?

00:18:11.355 --> 00:18:13.111
I'm moving back to my own place soon.

00:18:35.980 --> 00:18:38.060
It feels like I'm being
left here alone again.

00:18:41.060 --> 00:18:42.420
Why would you think that?

00:18:47.140 --> 00:18:47.860
When I was little,

00:18:47.860 --> 00:18:49.420
I was always left home alone.

00:18:51.620 --> 00:18:54.100
So, when I stayed in dorms at school,

00:18:54.100 --> 00:18:54.820
I felt like

00:18:55.900 --> 00:18:58.180
it was so nice having roommates
around all the time.

00:19:00.820 --> 00:19:02.620
Later, when I lived with you guys,

00:19:03.380 --> 00:19:04.980
I was really happy too.

00:19:06.700 --> 00:19:08.980
Before going to bed and after waking up,

00:19:09.340 --> 00:19:10.380
I was never alone.

00:19:16.140 --> 00:19:17.500
If that's really how you feel,

00:19:18.300 --> 00:19:21.100
maybe you really aren't suited
to writing novels alone.

00:19:23.260 --> 00:19:25.220
Because it's one
of the loneliest jobs there is.

00:19:28.900 --> 00:19:31.340
Would having AI around
make it any better?

00:19:31.666 --> 00:19:33.140
That would only make it lonelier.

00:19:34.300 --> 00:19:35.100
Just my opinion.

00:19:49.820 --> 00:19:50.620
Living alone

00:19:50.900 --> 00:19:52.740
is something every one
of us has to face.

00:19:54.220 --> 00:19:54.980
Well said.

00:19:56.740 --> 00:19:57.140
Cheers.

00:20:50.111 --> 00:20:52.210
Hello, ma'am. Your things have already
been brought up.

00:20:52.220 --> 00:20:52.890
Okay, thank you.

00:20:52.890 --> 00:20:53.666
You're welcome.

00:21:32.980 --> 00:21:33.700
Hello, Dai Shan.

00:21:38.380 --> 00:21:40.060
Sorry, I'm in the middle
of moving today,

00:21:40.333 --> 00:21:42.822
and later I still have to visit my mom
at the hospital.

00:21:42.844 --> 00:21:44.933
I probably won't be able
to make it over today.

00:21:49.977 --> 00:21:51.333
I'm at the Pingyue Hotel.

00:22:18.740 --> 00:22:20.580
So you picked up the habit from He Han,

00:22:21.100 --> 00:22:22.580
living in hotels instead of at home.

00:22:23.940 --> 00:22:24.980
I sold the apartment,

00:22:25.780 --> 00:22:26.700
so staying at a hotel

00:22:27.111 --> 00:22:28.660
is just temporary while I transition.

00:22:30.420 --> 00:22:31.222
Sorry about that.

00:22:31.820 --> 00:22:33.180
You're already such a big boss now,

00:22:33.377 --> 00:22:34.900
and I still had you come all this way.

00:22:37.400 --> 00:22:39.940
Liu Bei visited Zhuge Liang three times
before winning him over.

00:22:39.940 --> 00:22:41.911
What I've done
is nothing compared to that.

00:22:43.111 --> 00:22:45.400
I heard recently, you've
been working on theme extraction,

00:22:45.420 --> 00:22:46.220
content analysis,

00:22:46.780 --> 00:22:47.300
and even

00:22:47.460 --> 00:22:48.740
rhythm and pacing control.

00:22:49.020 --> 00:22:50.100
Your AI software

00:22:50.110 --> 00:22:51.540
is already capable to a large extent

00:22:51.780 --> 00:22:53.220
of replacing human editors.

00:22:53.577 --> 00:22:54.244
That's right.

00:22:54.780 --> 00:22:56.260
I don't need human editors,

00:22:56.260 --> 00:22:57.860
but I do need human authors.

00:22:58.580 --> 00:23:00.060
There are plenty of companies in China

00:23:00.060 --> 00:23:01.600
working on AI-generated writing.

00:23:01.860 --> 00:23:04.700
But I'm the only one
who is capable of pairing

00:23:04.860 --> 00:23:07.380
top-tier authors with AI to create

00:23:07.700 --> 00:23:08.980
something truly powerful.

00:23:10.911 --> 00:23:13.333
I've worked in the online
fiction industry for so many years.

00:23:13.466 --> 00:23:15.620
Of course, I know that AI writing alone,

00:23:15.620 --> 00:23:17.460
combined with inexperienced newcomers,

00:23:17.860 --> 00:23:19.740
can't produce top-tier work.

00:23:20.460 --> 00:23:21.580
I've already quit.

00:23:22.540 --> 00:23:23.380
So, on my end,

00:23:23.540 --> 00:23:25.866
I don't have the kind
of authors you're looking for.

00:23:26.180 --> 00:23:27.140
And to be blunt,

00:23:27.740 --> 00:23:29.220
I don't have any authors left at all.

00:23:30.140 --> 00:23:30.900
So, I'm afraid

00:23:31.220 --> 00:23:32.460
this trip of yours was wasted.

00:23:32.740 --> 00:23:34.140
You're the top-tier author yourself,

00:23:34.700 --> 00:23:35.700
Phantom Knight.

00:23:43.060 --> 00:23:44.540
Drop the act, Phantom Knight.

00:23:46.980 --> 00:23:48.060
Who told you that?

00:23:50.580 --> 00:23:52.020
When Gu Yan was continuing

00:23:52.020 --> 00:23:53.300
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui,

00:23:53.300 --> 00:23:54.060
to outsiders,

00:23:54.060 --> 00:23:56.020
it looked like
the perfect opportunity.

00:23:56.380 --> 00:23:57.530
Normally,

00:23:57.530 --> 00:24:00.060
an editor or an agent
would first read the original text.

00:24:00.740 --> 00:24:01.580
But you didn't.

00:24:02.100 --> 00:24:03.460
You directly decided

00:24:03.460 --> 00:24:05.140
to reject it on Gu Yan's behalf.

00:24:05.311 --> 00:24:06.844
There's only one reason for that.

00:24:08.220 --> 00:24:10.090
You've already
read the original text yourself.

00:24:10.090 --> 00:24:12.980
So, it means you and Phantom Knight

00:24:13.180 --> 00:24:14.340
are connected somehow.

00:24:20.740 --> 00:24:22.860
Honestly, companies in this industry

00:24:22.980 --> 00:24:24.780
all want Phantom Knight to come back.

00:24:25.020 --> 00:24:26.820
No matter what, it's still huge news.

00:24:27.140 --> 00:24:27.660
Look at Fan.

00:24:28.020 --> 00:24:29.140
He took an unfinished work

00:24:29.140 --> 00:24:30.500
by Phantom Knight

00:24:30.620 --> 00:24:31.860
and tied it to Gu Yan.

00:24:32.020 --> 00:24:33.980
And even now,
the buzz still hasn't died down.

00:24:34.620 --> 00:24:35.100
Of course,

00:24:35.980 --> 00:24:37.180
I think

00:24:38.060 --> 00:24:39.660
this work by Phantom Knight

00:24:39.660 --> 00:24:41.860
was weaker

00:24:41.955 --> 00:24:43.060
than her earlier standards.

00:24:44.020 --> 00:24:45.100
That may also be

00:24:45.100 --> 00:24:47.380
why she never wrote the second half.

00:24:50.580 --> 00:24:52.180
But we're a new company.

00:24:52.820 --> 00:24:55.220
So, we still want Phantom Knight
to come back.

00:24:55.740 --> 00:24:57.020
That's why I went to America

00:24:57.020 --> 00:24:59.300
to find your former editor, Ma.

00:25:02.740 --> 00:25:04.180
So Ma told you

00:25:04.420 --> 00:25:05.380
I'm Phantom Knight?

00:25:06.900 --> 00:25:08.500
Of course, he didn't tell me directly.

00:25:08.780 --> 00:25:09.540
But before I went,

00:25:09.540 --> 00:25:10.660
I'd already assumed

00:25:10.660 --> 00:25:13.100
you were Phantom Knight.

00:25:13.444 --> 00:25:15.890
Ma's getting older. He couldn't
hide his reaction fast enough.

00:25:16.180 --> 00:25:17.860
The moment I saw his expression,

00:25:18.940 --> 00:25:19.740
I knew I was right.

00:25:22.060 --> 00:25:24.420
I'd already heard Mr. Fan
and He Han say before

00:25:25.140 --> 00:25:26.460
that you're a smart woman.

00:25:27.755 --> 00:25:29.955
Turns out you're far smarter
than I thought.

00:25:35.420 --> 00:25:37.460
I'm here to invite you back.

00:25:37.940 --> 00:25:39.540
If you join our company

00:25:39.540 --> 00:25:40.900
as Phantom Knight,

00:25:41.540 --> 00:25:42.700
you'll become a shareholder.

00:25:44.020 --> 00:25:45.220
In the future,

00:25:45.444 --> 00:25:48.100
there will only be Lingqi Platform
in China, not Dingqi Platform,

00:25:48.180 --> 00:25:50.340
let alone companies
even smaller than Dingqi.

00:25:50.644 --> 00:25:52.740
Right now, Lingqi
is only in its expansion phase,

00:25:52.740 --> 00:25:54.180
so it needs you now.

00:25:55.180 --> 00:25:56.660
Once it's fully established,

00:25:56.660 --> 00:25:58.900
if you want to work with us later,

00:25:59.980 --> 00:26:00.700
the terms probably

00:26:00.700 --> 00:26:02.220
won't be this good anymore.

00:26:05.380 --> 00:26:06.060
First of all,

00:26:07.260 --> 00:26:08.420
I'm not Phantom Knight.

00:26:10.540 --> 00:26:11.260
Second,

00:26:11.740 --> 00:26:12.980
my future plans

00:26:13.355 --> 00:26:14.620
probably won't be in China.

00:26:16.700 --> 00:26:17.540
You're going abroad?

00:26:18.540 --> 00:26:19.020
Alone?

00:26:19.500 --> 00:26:19.940
Yes.

00:26:21.900 --> 00:26:23.380
Does He Han know about your plans?

00:26:25.140 --> 00:26:25.580
Yes.

00:26:29.100 --> 00:26:29.420
Alright.

00:26:30.340 --> 00:26:31.460
Think it over again anyway.

00:26:31.460 --> 00:26:32.620
I'll contact you again.

00:26:32.780 --> 00:26:34.820
Honestly, I hope

00:26:35.820 --> 00:26:37.620
you, as Phantom Knight,

00:26:37.900 --> 00:26:39.900
and He Han will both sign
with our company.

00:26:40.780 --> 00:26:43.260
Even though you two
didn't get back together,

00:26:43.260 --> 00:26:45.220
if you're separated
by too much distance,

00:26:45.666 --> 00:26:47.333
you'll still find it hard to let go.

00:26:48.540 --> 00:26:50.060
If I'm not mistaken,

00:26:51.420 --> 00:26:52.300
He Han probably also

00:26:52.300 --> 00:26:53.500
turned down your offer.

00:26:54.220 --> 00:26:54.940
And as for Gu Yan,

00:26:55.780 --> 00:26:57.660
I'll make him repay

00:26:58.020 --> 00:27:00.180
the unhappiness he brought you tenfold.

00:27:03.060 --> 00:27:03.700
I believe Gu Yan

00:27:03.700 --> 00:27:05.700
isn't exactly happy these days either.

00:27:07.222 --> 00:27:09.420
You've also worked
with top-ranking authors before.

00:27:09.980 --> 00:27:11.420
You surely know how much of the time

00:27:11.420 --> 00:27:12.180
feels exciting,

00:27:12.580 --> 00:27:13.500
how much of it

00:27:13.980 --> 00:27:14.660
feels anxious,

00:27:15.460 --> 00:27:16.500
and how much of it

00:27:16.820 --> 00:27:17.820
feels empty and boring.

00:27:18.377 --> 00:27:19.700
You understand all of that.

00:27:25.660 --> 00:27:26.700
But winning

00:27:27.500 --> 00:27:28.860
always feels good.

00:27:29.700 --> 00:27:31.620
No matter how long that feeling lasts.

00:27:32.066 --> 00:27:33.177
Don't you agree?

00:27:34.460 --> 00:27:35.180
Lin Zhanqiao,

00:27:36.380 --> 00:27:38.180
it's been a long time since you won.

00:27:38.900 --> 00:27:40.220
The same goes for He Han.

00:27:43.911 --> 00:27:45.088
I'm leaving.

00:27:50.222 --> 00:27:52.360
Oh, right, you still remember
Hong Qigong, don't you?

00:27:53.540 --> 00:27:55.060
She's already signed with our company.

00:27:55.780 --> 00:27:57.300
And your capable assistant, Mantou, too.

00:27:57.940 --> 00:27:59.220
He didn't go to Fan,

00:27:59.220 --> 00:28:00.900
and he didn't work
with Zhao Lanxin either.

00:28:01.420 --> 00:28:02.220
I signed him.

00:28:03.020 --> 00:28:05.620
He's at the company
learning the software system.

00:28:25.900 --> 00:28:28.340
(Tracing Back)

00:28:28.340 --> 00:28:30.940
(I Sell Pancakes in a Paranormal World)

00:28:46.180 --> 00:28:46.740
Lanxin,

00:28:48.420 --> 00:28:48.820
you...

00:28:49.100 --> 00:28:49.900
I already have

00:28:49.900 --> 00:28:52.260
three authors here
who've been signed away by Dai Shan.

00:28:52.580 --> 00:28:55.140
Please keep an eye on Gu Yan, okay?

00:28:55.580 --> 00:28:56.820
I'm with him right now.

00:28:57.700 --> 00:28:58.860
Dai Shan did approach Gu Yan,

00:28:59.260 --> 00:29:00.420
but Gu Yan turned her down.

00:29:03.620 --> 00:29:03.900
Good.

00:29:06.180 --> 00:29:07.700
It's rare to hear Mr. Fan this anxious.

00:29:10.260 --> 00:29:11.500
Dai Shan is going to

00:29:11.500 --> 00:29:13.000
sign a lot of authors immediately.

00:29:13.180 --> 00:29:14.340
But she won't have the energy

00:29:14.340 --> 00:29:16.177
to handle that many authors all at once.

00:29:16.660 --> 00:29:17.820
So, if you go over there,

00:29:17.888 --> 00:29:20.466
you'll be facing all the chaos
of a startup company.

00:29:22.260 --> 00:29:23.060
I don't have to go.

00:29:23.780 --> 00:29:24.780
Our partnership

00:29:25.222 --> 00:29:26.400
has been working pretty well,

00:29:26.540 --> 00:29:26.900
right?

00:29:29.540 --> 00:29:29.980
Of course.

00:29:31.260 --> 00:29:32.340
And I'll also do my best

00:29:32.700 --> 00:29:34.020
to put your feelings first.

00:29:42.422 --> 00:29:43.420
I have one condition.

00:29:47.900 --> 00:29:48.755
Let's hear it.

00:29:50.460 --> 00:29:51.660
I want to be your boss.

00:29:53.980 --> 00:29:55.220
What do you mean?

00:29:56.020 --> 00:29:57.460
You're the one who needs me more now.

00:29:58.688 --> 00:30:00.220
You're an author signed under me.

00:30:00.860 --> 00:30:02.380
We have an agreement between us.

00:30:05.044 --> 00:30:07.259
I don't know the exact details
of how you'd make it happen,

00:30:07.260 --> 00:30:08.660
but I only know what I want.

00:30:09.620 --> 00:30:10.890
I want to be your boss.

00:30:10.890 --> 00:30:12.060
You work for me.

00:30:15.300 --> 00:30:16.620
Do you even hear yourself?

00:30:18.780 --> 00:30:19.820
That's impossible.

00:30:22.580 --> 00:30:23.420
I'll tell Mr. Fan

00:30:23.780 --> 00:30:24.740
the condition too.

00:30:24.900 --> 00:30:25.500
Impossible.

00:30:25.600 --> 00:30:26.955
Even he couldn't make that happen.

00:30:34.777 --> 00:30:36.580
I advise you not to get ideas like that.

00:30:37.155 --> 00:30:39.533
We can discuss other ways
of working together.

00:30:39.860 --> 00:30:40.740
Other ways?

00:30:42.000 --> 00:30:43.600
I could discuss that with Dai Shan too.

00:30:45.100 --> 00:30:45.700
Wang Hai,

00:30:46.540 --> 00:30:48.500
only I get to threaten people.

00:30:49.220 --> 00:30:50.580
Nobody threatens me.

00:30:51.780 --> 00:30:53.060
If you keep pushing your luck,

00:30:53.060 --> 00:30:53.660
I'll show you

00:30:53.660 --> 00:30:55.540
what it means to rise and fall together.

00:30:56.580 --> 00:30:57.020
If I win,

00:30:57.420 --> 00:30:58.420
I can win alone.

00:30:58.866 --> 00:31:00.955
But if I lose, I will drag
someone down with me.

00:31:01.022 --> 00:31:03.044
And what exactly
do you think you have on me?

00:31:21.020 --> 00:31:22.740
(Zhao Lanxin)

00:31:22.980 --> 00:31:23.300
Hello?

00:31:25.500 --> 00:31:25.820
Hello?

00:31:28.820 --> 00:31:29.100
Hello?

00:31:30.740 --> 00:31:31.220
Gu Yan?

00:31:31.620 --> 00:31:32.700
What happened?

00:31:36.400 --> 00:31:38.266
Mr. Fan, I called the wrong number.

00:31:42.540 --> 00:31:43.420
Thanks.

00:31:44.511 --> 00:31:46.311
The sweet and sour pork
looks pretty good.

00:31:46.377 --> 00:31:46.866
Yeah.

00:31:47.980 --> 00:31:48.740
Let me try one.

00:31:49.466 --> 00:31:50.422
It's Ms. Zhao.

00:31:51.577 --> 00:31:52.355
Ms. Zhao.

00:31:56.133 --> 00:31:58.355
What are you talking about?
You seem really into it.

00:31:58.820 --> 00:32:00.540
We're preparing to
deal with the changes

00:32:00.600 --> 00:32:02.644
Lingqi Platform
may bring to future marketing.

00:32:02.820 --> 00:32:04.644
The main thing
is still reader targeting.

00:32:07.180 --> 00:32:08.580
You drove Xiaoxue home last night?

00:32:13.111 --> 00:32:15.377
She worked overtime
for the company until after 10 PM.

00:32:15.422 --> 00:32:16.890
It wasn't safe for her to go home alone.

00:32:16.900 --> 00:32:17.933
So, I had to drive her.

00:32:18.222 --> 00:32:20.422
Besides, you installed
surveillance cameras in the car.

00:32:20.460 --> 00:32:21.844
You saw everything yourself.

00:32:26.911 --> 00:32:27.860
Yesterday afternoon,

00:32:28.177 --> 00:32:29.250
you bought afternoon tea

00:32:29.250 --> 00:32:30.980
for Xiaoxue and the others on her team.

00:32:31.111 --> 00:32:32.933
The whole company got some. You did too.

00:32:32.980 --> 00:32:35.377
It just so happened that you sent
the one Xiaoxue likes most.

00:32:35.420 --> 00:32:37.355
I asked everyone
what they wanted to drink,

00:32:37.420 --> 00:32:38.860
and Xiaoxue made a suggestion.

00:32:38.860 --> 00:32:39.500
So I bought it.

00:32:39.500 --> 00:32:41.355
If you think it was inappropriate,
I won't do it again.

00:32:43.244 --> 00:32:45.466
Lingqi Platform is gaining momentum
so quickly right now.

00:32:45.550 --> 00:32:47.822
People in the company
are feeling unstable emotionally.

00:32:47.911 --> 00:32:49.288
I need to reassure them somehow.

00:32:49.355 --> 00:32:50.733
There's nothing wrong with that.

00:32:54.780 --> 00:32:55.780
She's a good employee.

00:32:56.900 --> 00:32:58.220
Don't make me lose her

00:32:59.060 --> 00:32:59.700
because of you.

00:33:01.300 --> 00:33:01.980
It won't happen.

00:33:02.444 --> 00:33:03.860
Yuan asked me to look after her.

00:33:04.155 --> 00:33:05.780
The industry's in bad shape right now.

00:33:05.955 --> 00:33:07.350
If we want to keep our investors steady,

00:33:07.380 --> 00:33:08.822
we'll mostly have to rely on Yuan.

00:33:08.830 --> 00:33:10.450
At a time like this,
would firing her for no reason

00:33:10.460 --> 00:33:10.930
be appropriate?

00:33:10.940 --> 00:33:13.111
You said it yourself,
the industry's struggling now.

00:33:14.100 --> 00:33:16.500
What if I introduced Xiaoxue
to a better opportunity?

00:33:17.420 --> 00:33:18.500
Do you think Yuan

00:33:18.500 --> 00:33:19.700
would be thanking me instead?

00:33:22.940 --> 00:33:23.380
Fair point.

00:33:31.020 --> 00:33:31.580
But honestly,

00:33:32.540 --> 00:33:33.220
in this company,

00:33:34.466 --> 00:33:35.460
the women I find

00:33:35.460 --> 00:33:37.220
cute, smart, and kind

00:33:38.200 --> 00:33:39.380
aren't just limited to her.

00:33:41.088 --> 00:33:42.355
People always need

00:33:42.755 --> 00:33:44.200
some kind of emotional outlet.

00:33:45.933 --> 00:33:48.180
If I can't get
emotional fulfillment in one place,

00:33:48.180 --> 00:33:49.740
I'll look for it somewhere else.

00:33:51.200 --> 00:33:52.688
As for who that person is,

00:33:53.800 --> 00:33:54.777
that part doesn't matter.

00:33:58.900 --> 00:34:00.020
Mr. Ling, Ms. Zhao,

00:34:00.022 --> 00:34:01.990
we've finished eating.
We'll head back to the office first.

00:34:02.020 --> 00:34:02.977
Please enjoy your meal.

00:34:03.066 --> 00:34:03.933
We'll get going now.

00:34:03.980 --> 00:34:04.340
Bye-bye.

00:34:06.100 --> 00:34:06.500
Xiaoxue,

00:34:08.155 --> 00:34:09.911
I think the ideas
you mentioned are good.

00:34:09.977 --> 00:34:11.540
But if we're putting them
into the proposal,

00:34:11.540 --> 00:34:12.822
they still need some refinement.

00:34:12.866 --> 00:34:14.400
Let's aim to make it
as strong as possible.

00:34:14.420 --> 00:34:14.740
Okay?

00:34:15.711 --> 00:34:16.555
Alright.

00:34:17.060 --> 00:34:17.380
Bye-bye.

00:34:41.060 --> 00:34:41.620
What happened?

00:34:42.020 --> 00:34:42.660
Who hit you?

00:34:46.780 --> 00:34:47.460
Who hit you?

00:34:48.700 --> 00:34:49.100
Come here.

00:34:51.355 --> 00:34:52.444
Let's talk inside.

00:34:57.700 --> 00:34:58.700
How did you find out?

00:34:59.100 --> 00:34:59.980
Zhao Lanxin told me.

00:35:00.740 --> 00:35:01.460
Who hit you?

00:35:09.500 --> 00:35:09.980
Er Jiu.

00:35:14.940 --> 00:35:15.500
Er Jiu?

00:35:16.420 --> 00:35:16.900
Why?

00:35:18.666 --> 00:35:20.244
He lost money gambling.

00:35:20.333 --> 00:35:21.900
He came to the internet cafe
looking for money from me.

00:35:21.900 --> 00:35:23.555
I refused to give him any, so he hit me.

00:35:23.580 --> 00:35:24.800
It wasn't the first time.

00:35:25.980 --> 00:35:27.420
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

00:35:30.260 --> 00:35:31.340
Zhao Lanxin said telling you

00:35:31.340 --> 00:35:32.740
would only create more trouble.

00:35:32.844 --> 00:35:34.622
She said she'd handle
our problems herself.

00:35:34.777 --> 00:35:36.022
Where's Er Jiu now?

00:35:39.444 --> 00:35:40.400
I don't know.

00:35:40.711 --> 00:35:41.620
He has a concussion.

00:35:41.630 --> 00:35:42.530
His head was split open.

00:35:42.540 --> 00:35:43.822
Zhao Lanxin took him away.

00:35:47.420 --> 00:35:48.580
A concussion? Why?

00:35:49.740 --> 00:35:50.180
I hit him.

00:35:51.820 --> 00:35:52.540
You hit him?

00:35:55.460 --> 00:35:56.140
He hit me first.

00:35:56.288 --> 00:35:58.540
He was choking me so hard
I could barely breathe.

00:35:58.540 --> 00:35:59.866
Only then did I fight back.

00:36:00.600 --> 00:36:02.066
I smashed him with an ashtray.

00:36:05.688 --> 00:36:07.222
I'm going to find Zhao Lanxin.

00:36:17.933 --> 00:36:18.822
Where's Er Jiu?

00:36:27.540 --> 00:36:28.180
He's inside.

00:36:31.980 --> 00:36:32.980
I hired a caregiver,

00:36:33.340 --> 00:36:34.380
and they will come every day

00:36:34.580 --> 00:36:35.820
to take care of him

00:36:36.488 --> 00:36:37.933
and help with his recovery.

00:36:41.022 --> 00:36:42.380
How long until he recovers?

00:36:42.955 --> 00:36:44.400
Two or three weeks, probably.

00:36:46.980 --> 00:36:48.340
A scalp laceration

00:36:48.500 --> 00:36:49.500
and a mild concussion.

00:36:50.580 --> 00:36:51.380
The doctor said

00:36:51.540 --> 00:36:52.820
it looked scary,

00:36:53.244 --> 00:36:55.955
but actually San Mei's injuries
were more serious.

00:36:56.244 --> 00:36:57.755
Did you call the police at the time?

00:36:58.100 --> 00:36:58.540
Yes.

00:37:00.100 --> 00:37:01.900
The police gave Er Jiu
a disciplinary lecture

00:37:01.900 --> 00:37:03.140
and a warning notice.

00:37:03.577 --> 00:37:05.244
I've already hired a lawyer.

00:37:06.220 --> 00:37:07.340
San Mei acted in self-defense.

00:37:08.580 --> 00:37:09.740
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

00:37:12.540 --> 00:37:13.820
Didn't San Mei already say it?

00:37:14.660 --> 00:37:16.460
She was afraid of causing you trouble.

00:37:16.860 --> 00:37:18.180
The first time he became violent,

00:37:18.660 --> 00:37:20.380
I should've made San Mei
divorce this animal.

00:37:23.220 --> 00:37:24.620
But have you ever thought about this?

00:37:25.820 --> 00:37:27.900
Weren't the two of them
actually very close before?

00:37:28.177 --> 00:37:30.220
Why did things
become like this after marriage?

00:37:31.111 --> 00:37:33.140
If Er Jiu were really
some violent monster,

00:37:33.820 --> 00:37:35.980
then how did you
spend over ten years with him

00:37:36.177 --> 00:37:37.380
without ever realizing

00:37:37.380 --> 00:37:39.266
he could hurt someone close to him?

00:37:42.500 --> 00:37:42.980
Why?

00:37:44.340 --> 00:37:46.580
Because the person San Mei
loves isn't him. It's you.

00:37:49.380 --> 00:37:50.420
Now that I've told you,

00:37:50.466 --> 00:37:51.860
what are you planning to do?

00:37:52.900 --> 00:37:53.980
Because of you,

00:37:54.300 --> 00:37:56.460
Er Jiu and San Mei
have both suffered so much.

00:37:59.220 --> 00:38:00.220
If they get divorced

00:38:00.740 --> 00:38:02.260
and San Mei ends up alone again,

00:38:02.688 --> 00:38:04.460
shouldn't you
take responsibility for her?

00:38:22.140 --> 00:38:23.260
So,

00:38:23.555 --> 00:38:25.488
the thing you think can threaten me

00:38:25.820 --> 00:38:27.020
is San Mei and Er Jiu?

00:38:27.700 --> 00:38:28.260
Isn't it?

00:38:29.580 --> 00:38:31.300
They're the people you care about most,

00:38:31.900 --> 00:38:34.060
and also the two people
you believe you've hurt the most.

00:38:51.844 --> 00:38:53.288
You haven't eaten yet, right?

00:38:53.620 --> 00:38:54.780
I haven't eaten all day.

00:38:55.820 --> 00:38:57.220
That's all you brought?

00:38:58.222 --> 00:39:00.488
I already sent
everything else back home.

00:39:01.340 --> 00:39:02.580
My dad's leaving this weekend.

00:39:02.740 --> 00:39:04.444
I won't be staying here much longer.

00:39:10.060 --> 00:39:10.620
How will you

00:39:10.620 --> 00:39:11.980
move all this by yourself?

00:39:13.020 --> 00:39:14.420
Zhang Yousen happened to come see me,

00:39:14.580 --> 00:39:15.500
so I asked him to help.

00:39:17.460 --> 00:39:18.580
Hasn't he already decided

00:39:18.580 --> 00:39:20.555
to stay with
that entrepreneur girlfriend of his?

00:39:20.820 --> 00:39:21.780
And he came here,

00:39:21.780 --> 00:39:23.022
still unable to let you go?

00:39:23.740 --> 00:39:25.420
That entrepreneur girlfriend of his

00:39:25.711 --> 00:39:27.300
actually offered him a huge opportunity.

00:39:28.500 --> 00:39:30.020
Catherine said she could help me become

00:39:30.020 --> 00:39:31.888
the head of the new
Hong Kong, China branch.

00:39:32.340 --> 00:39:33.740
Handling all of that alone

00:39:33.900 --> 00:39:34.940
would be a lot of pressure,

00:39:35.066 --> 00:39:36.220
but the prospects are good.

00:39:36.844 --> 00:39:38.511
So you're going to Hong Kong, China?

00:39:38.900 --> 00:39:39.620
I'm going with her.

00:39:40.688 --> 00:39:42.060
But I already broke up with her.

00:39:43.511 --> 00:39:44.920
I told her every time I saw you again,

00:39:44.940 --> 00:39:46.488
it still felt exactly like before.

00:39:46.844 --> 00:39:47.780
So I wanted to ask you,

00:39:48.111 --> 00:39:50.311
is there even the slightest chance
you'd want me to stay?

00:39:56.666 --> 00:39:57.820
An opportunity like this

00:39:57.940 --> 00:39:59.580
is something you might not reach

00:39:59.580 --> 00:40:01.088
even after working 10 or 15 years.

00:40:03.220 --> 00:40:04.740
So I can't ask you to stay for me.

00:40:11.533 --> 00:40:12.822
What are you thinking about?

00:40:17.060 --> 00:40:17.620
He Han.

00:40:19.580 --> 00:40:20.340
I'm not like him.

00:40:22.288 --> 00:40:23.940
I never loved Zhang Yousen that deeply,

00:40:24.155 --> 00:40:25.180
so I can let him go.

00:40:27.020 --> 00:40:28.100
But He Han loves you.

00:40:28.180 --> 00:40:29.260
Even an idiot can see it.

00:40:30.620 --> 00:40:31.220
You and he

00:40:31.488 --> 00:40:32.700
are like a pair of hedgehogs.

00:40:33.500 --> 00:40:34.700
When you get too close,

00:40:34.780 --> 00:40:35.780
even if you don't mean to,

00:40:35.933 --> 00:40:37.666
you still end up hurting each other.

00:40:39.666 --> 00:40:41.133
But maybe that's not such a bad thing.

00:40:42.380 --> 00:40:43.100
I think

00:40:43.740 --> 00:40:45.620
after everything we've been through,

00:40:46.200 --> 00:40:48.244
the future version of me
will become better.

00:40:49.220 --> 00:40:50.100
Because I've matured.

00:40:51.220 --> 00:40:51.940
You've matured,

00:40:52.111 --> 00:40:53.222
but he hasn't.

00:40:55.377 --> 00:40:57.580
Children who never
received proper love growing up

00:40:57.580 --> 00:40:58.620
often don't know

00:40:59.400 --> 00:41:01.177
how to express their feelings as adults

00:41:01.740 --> 00:41:03.740
because they never
had anyone to learn from.

00:41:04.133 --> 00:41:06.000
So they simply stop loving altogether.

00:41:06.700 --> 00:41:08.180
That way, they can protect themselves

00:41:08.180 --> 00:41:09.533
and protect other people too.

00:41:09.644 --> 00:41:11.400
What scares them most is loving someone,

00:41:11.644 --> 00:41:13.333
because they'll inevitably ruin it.

00:41:14.000 --> 00:41:16.377
I think my dad
might be that kind of person too.

00:41:19.060 --> 00:41:20.140
This afternoon,

00:41:20.140 --> 00:41:22.488
I was planning to go over
and spend some time with her.

00:41:22.980 --> 00:41:24.660
But my dad insisted on sending me back.

00:41:26.220 --> 00:41:27.100
Because he believes

00:41:28.460 --> 00:41:29.100
a person

00:41:29.980 --> 00:41:30.970
should try their best

00:41:30.970 --> 00:41:32.260
not to become a burden to others.

00:41:34.020 --> 00:41:34.740
So in his mind,

00:41:34.740 --> 00:41:36.380
when it comes to taking care of my mom,

00:41:36.700 --> 00:41:38.340
having him there alone
is already enough.

00:41:42.180 --> 00:41:43.500
So when it comes to being parents

00:41:44.260 --> 00:41:45.220
and raising children,

00:41:45.220 --> 00:41:47.020
your mom and my dad

00:41:48.020 --> 00:41:49.340
are complete opposites.

00:41:57.620 --> 00:41:59.060
Sometimes I wonder,

00:42:00.980 --> 00:42:01.980
in this world,

00:42:02.900 --> 00:42:04.500
is there even such a thing as

00:42:05.140 --> 00:42:06.500
a textbook-perfect and happy family?

00:42:08.620 --> 00:42:09.380
Probably not.

00:42:13.555 --> 00:42:15.300
We need to discuss something with you.

00:42:16.740 --> 00:42:18.740
The patient's
current condition isn't very good.

00:42:19.460 --> 00:42:20.820
Please take a look at this notice.

00:42:21.933 --> 00:42:23.155
If you've made your decision

00:42:23.300 --> 00:42:24.844
and choose to stop her treatment,

00:42:25.780 --> 00:42:27.180
you only need to sign the last page.

00:42:38.900 --> 00:42:41.300
(I voluntarily accept the risks caused
by refusing or giving up treatment.)

00:42:41.300 --> 00:42:43.060
(Signature of authorized family member)

00:42:45.720 --> 00:42:51.680
(Patient-authorized family member's
signature: Lin Xiangdong, Relationship: Husband)

00:43:05.921 --> 00:43:07.041
(I've been thinking.)

00:43:08.321 --> 00:43:11.601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

00:43:12.361 --> 00:43:19.691
(is probably different.)

00:43:20.691 --> 00:43:22.441
♪If the sky♪

00:43:22.951 --> 00:43:24.351
♪And the sea♪

00:43:24.891 --> 00:43:26.601
♪Turned upside down♪

00:43:28.161 --> 00:43:30.091
♪If a swimming fish♪

00:43:30.491 --> 00:43:33.881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

00:43:35.651 --> 00:43:37.621
♪If back then♪

00:43:37.981 --> 00:43:42.391
♪We had never let go♪

00:43:42.991 --> 00:43:49.271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

00:43:50.391 --> 00:43:52.541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

00:43:52.541 --> 00:43:54.411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

00:43:54.591 --> 00:43:57.031
♪And found our way back whole♪

00:43:57.871 --> 00:44:00.041
♪So let this surging love♪

00:44:00.041 --> 00:44:04.471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

00:44:05.371 --> 00:44:07.551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

00:44:07.551 --> 00:44:08.641
♪That's alright♪

00:44:09.181 --> 00:44:09.931
♪If we're buried♪

00:44:09.931 --> 00:44:12.631
♪By passing years all the better♪

00:44:12.891 --> 00:44:15.071
♪At least we still can keep♪

00:44:15.251 --> 00:44:19.671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

00:44:35.431 --> 00:44:37.721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

00:44:37.721 --> 00:44:39.481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

00:44:39.601 --> 00:44:42.071
♪Searching all along the way♪

00:44:42.871 --> 00:44:45.031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

00:44:45.221 --> 00:44:50.131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

00:44:50.131 --> 00:44:53.651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

00:44:53.891 --> 00:44:54.861
♪Only after loss♪

00:44:54.861 --> 00:44:57.491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

00:44:57.901 --> 00:45:00.261
♪In another time and space♪

00:45:00.261 --> 00:45:01.821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

00:45:01.821 --> 00:45:04.651
♪Till we grow old♪

00:45:05.611 --> 00:45:07.901
♪But still the sky will never♪

00:45:07.901 --> 00:45:10.571
♪Turn with the sea♪

00:45:13.091 --> 00:45:15.501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

00:45:15.501 --> 00:45:20.711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪